  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Safety Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Identify and rectify unsafe acts and unsafe conditions at the worksite</p></li><li><p>Conduct regular site inspections and ensure corrective actions are implemented</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with Workplace Safety & Health (WSH) regulations and company policies</p></li><li><p>Enforce all WSH requirements and in-house safety rules</p></li><li><p>Assist in accident/incident investigations and reporting</p></li><li><p>Conduct safety training, toolbox meetings, briefings, and safety time-outs</p></li><li><p>Liaise with project teams and contractors on safety and health matters</p></li><li><p>Monitor SHE performance and follow up on safety documentation</p></li><li><p>Perform other duties as assigned</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Advanced Certificate in WSH Level B and/or relevant safety certifications</p></li><li><p>Minimum 3 years’ experience in high-rise building projects</p></li><li><p>Good interpersonal and communication skills</p></li><li><p>Able to work in a fast-paced environment and under pressure</p></li><li><p>Willing to work at night shifts</p></li><li><p>6-day work week</p></li></ul>",
